<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-922-760  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 922 760.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 27 1989 v6 n47 p21(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Better communications lets firms farm out work.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tagare, Sunil.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Improved worldwide communications are making it easier for somelarge US companies to send out some of their white collar jobs toother countries.andP;  Satellite technology and fiber optics have madeit possible for companies to save large amounts of money by havinginformation entered into computers from remote locations.andO;American Airlines is given credit for starting a trend by havingaccounting information entered into computers by workers inBarbados.andP;  The information is then sent to the Airline's Tulsa,OK, data processing center.andP;  The airline reportedly saved from 50to 60 percent of its costs as a result of the installation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     International CommunicationsTransmission LinesOutsourcingData EntryCost Benefit Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>